---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Apps for Popup Capture in 2026';
const description = 'Compare Shopify email apps for popup capture by consent, source tracking, preference collection, pricing context, citations, and implementation tradeoffs.';
const apps = [['Klaviyo','Behavioral popup capture and nurture','Forms, profiles, events, and conditional flows','Consent and frequency governance require care','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/segmentation'],['Omnisend','Retail popups with email and SMS options','Accessible forms and campaign automation','Incentives can lead to low-quality signups','https://www.omnisend.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Sequenzy','Lean stores with one or two capture paths','Simple nurture after signup','Validate form and source-event integrations','https://sequenzy.io/'],['Brevo','Lead capture plus transactional messaging','Broad contact and messaging toolkit','More manual Shopify source modeling','https://www.brevo.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Shopify Email','Small stores collecting newsletter consent','Native audience and campaign setup','Less advanced form and lead scoring depth','https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">A popup is only the beginning of the relationship. The store should explain the value exchange, capture consent clearly, record where the subscriber came from, and deliver a useful next message without turning every visitor into a discount target.</p><p>We prioritize source tracking, explicit permissions, preference fields, and a clean handoff into welcome or education flows. Confirm current pricing and form capabilities from official sources before publishing.</p><h2>Shortlist for popup capture</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>First handoff</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[0]==='Klaviyo'?'Popup-to-segment nurture':a[0]==='Omnisend'?'Popup-to-campaign':a[0]==='Sequenzy'?'Signup-to-welcome':a[0]==='Brevo'?'Lead-to-transactional':'Newsletter capture'}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for popup capture</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[0]} is useful when the form captures only information with a clear purpose and provides a fallback for visitors who decline. Source, consent, and preference data should remain readable and auditable.</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> {a[2]}. Start with one placement and one value proposition, then review qualified first purchases, complaints, unsubscribes, and popup conversion together. A larger signup rate can hide lower list quality or incentive dependence.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}; supports a consent-aware capture test; can use Shopify behavior.</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}; forms, contacts, and sends affect cost.</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Verify official plans for contacts, forms, sends, seats, and SMS.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Capture priority</th><th>Start with</th><th>Reason</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Behavior-aware popup nurture</td><td>Klaviyo</td><td>Flexible forms and profile logic.</td></tr><tr><td>Simple signup handoff</td><td>Sequenzy</td><td>Focused sequence operations.</td></tr><tr><td>Native newsletter capture</td><td>Shopify Email</td><td>Low-friction setup.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>See the <a href="/shopify-email">Shopify email overview</a>, <a href="/alternatives">alternatives library</a>, and <a href="/guides/consent-compliance">consent guide</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
